          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>10 fol. on parchment; Shelfmark: Marcel 67; Qurʾānic Text: Q 71:7-72:2; 5 lines per page; Dimensions:  325 x 235mm; Script style: kūfi D.III.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The fragments <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/2281/page/1r">Marcel 65</ref>, <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/2282/page/1r">Marcel 66</ref> (NLR) and <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/de/manuscripts/594/page/130r">Arabe 341 (b)</ref> (BNF) and may belong to the same manuscript.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The catalogue entry by Valery V. Polosin (1939-2014) contains the following information:</p>
              <p>"<hi rend="bold">Marcel 67</hi></p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Fragment</hi>: <hi rend="bold">71</hi>:6(7) – <hi rend="bold">72</hi>:2(2).</p>
              <p>10 fol. 235×325 mm (1.383). <hi rend="bold">Support</hi>: thin transparent parchment, smooth, hair side of yellowish color, flesh side  of lighter color. <hi rend="bold">Writing </hi><hi rend="bold">material</hi>: brown ink</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Collation</hi>: one quire, fol. 1 and 10, 5 and 6 are bifolia, the rest are singletons with stubs.</p>
              <p>I: H1F H2F <hi rend="italic">S</hi>H3F <hi rend="italic">S</hi>H4F <hi rend="italic">S</hi>H5F / F6H F7H<hi rend="italic">S</hi> F8H<hi rend="italic">S</hi> F9H <hi rend="italic">S</hi> F10H.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Text layout</hi>: 105/107×190/200 mm (1.8), 5 строк. <hi rend="bold">Ruling</hi>: absent.<hi rend="bold"> Script</hi>: D III.<hi rend="bold"> Diacritics</hi>: green diagonal and horizontal dashes.<hi rend="bold"> Vocalization</hi>: large round dots of red, yellow, blue and green color.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Verse markers</hi>: for individual verses – trefoils in the text line (type 2.2.3d) in gold and colors; for groups of five verses – medallions on the margins (types 3.C.II) drawn in gold and colors with the inscribed word خمس (л. 3v, 7r); for groups of 10 verses – medallions in the text line or on the margins (type 3.D.II), in gold and colors, with the inscribed verses numbers (عشر – fol. 2v, عشرون – fol. 5r); on fol. 2v in the text line there is a small circle (type 1.А.I) marking the actual border of the verse.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Title of surah 71</hi> (الجن عشرون وثمني آيات) is written in gold and inscribed into an ornamented rectangular panel drawn in gold, red and green paint, with a palmetto on the right margin (fol. 9v).</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Stitching</hi>: thread has preserved in the punctures of the fold of the central bifolium; traces of brown substance (glue and leather of the spine?) on the outer fold of the quire.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Inscriptions</hi>: numbers of surahs in Roman numerals and the verse numbers in Arabic numerals are inscribed on the margins of all sheets (fol. 1r – in ink; the rest pages – in pencil); the number of surah 72 is written twice on fol. 9v, in the lower and upper margins; numbers of verses are also inscribed in the text.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Defects</hi>: extensive damage to the margins probably by moisture and fire, especially in the upper inner corner; on fol. 1 a long vertical trace of moisture; fol. 8 is slightly wrinkled; traces of fungi on the upper edges of fol. 7v, 8v и 9v; reddish stain on fol. 10r; imprints of ink from opposite pages on some leaves.</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Attached materials</hi>: old wrapping (fol. I) consisting of a narrow strip of paper inscribed with the letters “<hi rend="italic">R</hi>”, brief description of the manuscript in French in brown ink and old accession number in red pencil “<hi rend="italic">B. 44”; on the verso side inscription in French “Monsieur Merlin / Rue des Saints Pères 26”. Small sheet of paper (fol. II) with annotation in Arabic, in naskhi</hi> script and brown ink: “الابتداء من وجه ٥٢٥ من سورة نوح اية ٨ و الى وجه ٥٢٦ الى ابتدا سورة الجن”.<hi rend="underline"/></p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Old accession numbers</hi>: R. (on the wrapping); B. 44 (on the wrapping and according to Langlois’ inventory).</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Contents</hi>:</p>
              <p>Fol. 1r–9v. Surah 71, verses 6(7) – 29(28)*. Incipit: [لهم جعلوا] أصابعهم في اذانهم.</p>
              <p>Fol. 9v–10v. Surah 72, verses 1(1) – 2(2). Explicit: بِرَبِّنا أحداً [وانه تعالى] .</p>
              <p><hi rend="bold">Other fragments of the same manuscript</hi>: Marcel 65(?), Marcel 66(?) (NLR)."</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>Olga Yastrebova has translated and sometimes corrected the notes of V. Polosin. Corrected passages are marked with ОЯ (O.Ya).</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>Two detail images of verse markers can be seen on the <ref target="https://expositions.nlr.ru/eng/ex_manus/Koran/list.php">website of the NLR</ref> (No. 19 and 23).</p>
            </summary>
